<p>was A3.<br/>This A3 classification is a horrible thing, for you are kept fooling about in the camp on fatigues, &amp; silly route marches, supposed to be hardening.  While on this classification I went up with O.T.C. forms &amp; he refused (Capt Myers) to sign them till the rib was healed.<br/>Two days afterwards I tore off the strapping &amp; again paraded with the forms.  This time he discovered lung trouble (imaginary) at the posterior right base.  A sputum test was taken &amp; the glorious old suspense business began in real earnest.<br/>No draft has left for about 2 months, so when word</p>
